gomodel:SYNGO_2136  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: immuno-EM demonstrates localization in spine head membrane of wild-type mice. integral to membrane localization based on near-membrane location in EM images and the protein having TMM domains.\n\nto clarify the terminology used in the paper for the \"perisynapse\" localization;\n\"Morphological studies have shown that both phospholipase C-β and DGL-α are localized to the perisynapse, a subdivision of the dendritic spine that forms a 100-200-nm-thick border around the postsynaptic density\". Experimental description: \"Male fmr1-/- mice (FVB.129P2-Fmr1tm1Cgr/J) and wild-type control mice (FVB.129P2-Pde6b+Tyrc-ch/AntJ) from Jackson Laboratories (Bar Harbor, ME), aged between 6 to 10 weeks, or adult male fmr1-/- mice on C57BL/6J background (Fmr1 KO2) were used for the biochemical studies.\"" , "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099055 replaced by GO:0045211" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_2136" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

